[["Map",1,2,77,78],"docs",["Map",3,4,17,18,28,29,39,40,50,51],"configuration",{"id":3,"data":5,"body":14,"filePath":15,"digest":16,"deferredRender":8},{"title":6,"description":7,"editUrl":8,"head":9,"template":10,"sidebar":11,"pagefind":8,"draft":12},"Configuration","Configure the astro-bunny-adapter.",true,[],"doc",{"hidden":12,"attrs":13},false,{},"The adapter accepts an optional configuration object.\n\n## `esbuild`\n\nAfter Astro builds your app, the adapter re-bundles the server output with\n[esbuild](https://esbuild.github.io/) so it runs in bunny.net's Deno-based\nedge runtime. Use this option to customize the esbuild configuration.\n\n### Merging with defaults\n\nPass an object to merge with the default esbuild options:\n\n```js\nimport { defineConfig } from \"astro/config\";\nimport bunny from \"astro-bunny-adapter\";\n\nexport default defineConfig({\n  output: \"server\",\n  adapter: bunny({\n    esbuild: {\n      minify: true,\n    },\n  }),\n});\n```\n\n### Full control\n\nPass a function to receive the default options and return your own:\n\n```js\nimport { defineConfig } from \"astro/config\";\nimport bunny from \"astro-bunny-adapter\";\n\nexport default defineConfig({\n  output: \"server\",\n  adapter: bunny({\n    esbuild: (defaults) => ({\n      ...defaults,\n      minify: true,\n      // add custom plugins, change target, etc.\n    }),\n  }),\n});\n```\n\n### Default esbuild options\n\nFor reference, the adapter uses these defaults:\n\n```js\n{\n  entryPoints: [entryFile],\n  outfile: outFile,\n  bundle: true,\n  format: \"esm\",\n  platform: \"browser\",\n  target: \"es2024\",\n  minify: false,\n  external: [\n    \"node:*\",\n    \"@bunny.net/edgescript-sdk\",\n    \"@bunny.net/edgescript-sdk/*\",\n  ],\n  logLevel: \"info\",\n}\n```\n\n## Image optimization\n\nAstro's default [Sharp](https://sharp.pixelplumbing.com/) image service is not\navailable in bunny.net's edge runtime. The adapter automatically detects this\nand switches to a passthrough (no-op) image service, logging a warning during\nthe build.\n\nIf you need image optimization, consider using bunny.net's built-in\n[Bunny Optimizer](https://docs.bunny.net/docs/stream-image-processing) on your\nPull Zone, or an external image CDN.","src/content/docs/configuration.mdx","07e33409720ce9ad","deploying",{"id":17,"data":19,"body":25,"filePath":26,"digest":27,"deferredRender":8},{"title":20,"description":21,"editUrl":8,"head":22,"template":10,"sidebar":23,"pagefind":8,"draft":12},"Deploying","Deploy your Astro site to bunny.net Edge Scripting.",[],{"hidden":12,"attrs":24},{},"After running `astro build`, you need to deploy two things:\n\n1. **Static assets** (`dist/client/`) to a Bunny Storage Zone\n2. **Server script** (`dist/server/entry.mjs`) to an Edge Script\n\n## bunny.net setup\n\nBefore deploying, set up the following in your\n[bunny.net dashboard](https://dash.bunny.net):\n\n1. **Storage Zone** — Create a storage zone to host your static assets\n   (CSS, JS, images, prerendered pages).\n2. **Pull Zone** — Create a pull zone linked to your storage zone. This serves\n   your static assets over bunny.net's CDN.\n3. **Middleware Edge Script** — Create a middleware edge script connected to\n   the pull zone. The middleware intercepts requests and renders dynamic pages\n   through Astro's SSR pipeline. Requests that don't match an Astro route are\n   passed through to the pull zone origin (your static assets).\n\n## Manual deployment\n\n### Upload static assets\n\nUpload the contents of `dist/client/` to your storage zone. You can use the\n[bunny.net dashboard](https://dash.bunny.net), the\n[Storage API](https://docs.bunny.net/reference/storage-api-overview), or any\ntool that supports the Bunny Storage API.\n\n### Deploy the edge script\n\nDeploy `dist/server/entry.mjs` to your edge script using the\n[Edge Scripting API](https://docs.bunny.net/docs/edge-scripting-api) or the\nbunny.net dashboard.\n\n## GitHub Actions\n\nHere's a complete workflow that builds and deploys on every push to `main`:\n\n```yaml\nname: Deploy\n\non:\n  push:\n    branches: [main]\n\njobs:\n  deploy:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n      - uses: actions/setup-node@v4\n        with:\n          node-version: 22\n          cache: npm\n\n      - run: npm ci\n\n      - name: Build\n        run: npm run build\n\n      - name: Upload static assets\n        env:\n          BUNNY_STORAGE_PASSWORD: ${{ secrets.BUNNY_STORAGE_PASSWORD }}\n          BUNNY_STORAGE_ZONE: ${{ secrets.BUNNY_STORAGE_ZONE }}\n        run: |\n          cd dist/client\n          find . -type f | while read -r file; do\n            path=\"${file#./}\"\n            curl -s -X PUT \\\n              -H \"AccessKey: $BUNNY_STORAGE_PASSWORD\" \\\n              -H \"Content-Type: application/octet-stream\" \\\n              --data-binary @\"$file\" \\\n              \"https://storage.bunnycdn.com/$BUNNY_STORAGE_ZONE/$path\" \\\n              --fail\n          done\n\n      - name: Deploy edge script\n        uses: BunnyWay/actions/deploy-script@main\n        with:\n          script_id: ${{ secrets.BUNNY_SCRIPT_ID }}\n          deploy_key: ${{ secrets.BUNNY_DEPLOY_KEY }}\n          file: dist/server/entry.mjs\n```\n\n### Required secrets\n\n| Secret | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `BUNNY_STORAGE_PASSWORD` | Storage Zone AccessKey (found in Storage Zone settings → FTP & API Access) |\n| `BUNNY_STORAGE_ZONE` | Name of your storage zone |\n| `BUNNY_SCRIPT_ID` | Edge Script ID (found in Edge Script settings) |\n| `BUNNY_DEPLOY_KEY` | Edge Script deploy key |","src/content/docs/deploying.mdx","3bba79bd8ee5ace7","getting-started",{"id":28,"data":30,"body":36,"filePath":37,"digest":38,"deferredRender":8},{"title":31,"description":32,"editUrl":8,"head":33,"template":10,"sidebar":34,"pagefind":8,"draft":12},"Getting Started","Install and configure astro-bunny-adapter to deploy your Astro site to bunny.net.",[],{"hidden":12,"attrs":35},{},"## Prerequisites\n\n- [Astro](https://astro.build) 6\n- Node.js 22.12.0 or later\n- A [bunny.net](https://bunny.net) account\n\n## Installation\n\nimport { Tabs, TabItem } from \"@astrojs/starlight/components\";\n\n\u003CTabs>\n  \u003CTabItem label=\"npm\">\n    ```bash\n    npm install astro-bunny-adapter\n    ```\n  \u003C/TabItem>\n  \u003CTabItem label=\"pnpm\">\n    ```bash\n    pnpm add astro-bunny-adapter\n    ```\n  \u003C/TabItem>\n  \u003CTabItem label=\"yarn\">\n    ```bash\n    yarn add astro-bunny-adapter\n    ```\n  \u003C/TabItem>\n\u003C/Tabs>\n\n## Configuration\n\nAdd the adapter to your `astro.config.mjs`:\n\n```js\n// astro.config.mjs\nimport { defineConfig } from \"astro/config\";\nimport bunny from \"astro-bunny-adapter\";\n\nexport default defineConfig({\n  output: \"server\",\n  adapter: bunny(),\n});\n```\n\n:::caution\n`output: \"server\"` is required. Static output is not supported because\nbunny.net Edge Scripting is designed for on-demand server rendering.\n:::\n\n## Build output\n\nRunning `astro build` produces two directories:\n\n```\ndist/\n├── client/   # Static assets (CSS, JS, images, prerendered pages)\n└── server/\n    └── entry.mjs   # Server entrypoint for Edge Scripting\n```\n\n- **`dist/client/`** — Upload these files to a [Bunny Storage Zone](https://docs.bunny.net/docs/storage-overview)\n  connected to your Pull Zone.\n- **`dist/server/entry.mjs`** — Deploy this file as your Edge Script.\n\nSee [Deploying](/deploying) for step-by-step instructions.","src/content/docs/getting-started.mdx","79ba78dac69da83f","how-it-works",{"id":39,"data":41,"body":47,"filePath":48,"digest":49,"deferredRender":8},{"title":42,"description":43,"editUrl":8,"head":44,"template":10,"sidebar":45,"pagefind":8,"draft":12},"How It Works","Understand how astro-bunny-adapter builds and serves your Astro site.",[],{"hidden":12,"attrs":46},{},"## Build pipeline\n\nWhen you run `astro build`, the adapter hooks into Astro's build process:\n\n1. **Astro builds your app** as usual in server mode, producing a `client/`\n   directory (static assets) and a `server/` directory (server code).\n\n2. **The adapter re-bundles the server output** with\n   [esbuild](https://esbuild.github.io/), targeting `platform: \"browser\"` so\n   the code runs in bunny.net's Deno-based edge runtime. All dependencies are\n   inlined into a single file, except for `node:*` built-ins and the\n   `@bunny.net/edgescript-sdk`.\n\n3. **Intermediate build artifacts are cleaned up**, leaving only the final\n   `entry.mjs` in `dist/server/`.\n\n## Request handling\n\nAt runtime, the edge script uses\n[`servePullZone().onOriginRequest()`](https://docs.bunny.net/scripting/middleware/overview)\nfrom the `@bunny.net/edgescript-sdk` to intercept incoming requests.\n\nFor each request:\n\n1. The handler checks if the request matches an Astro route.\n2. **If it matches** — Astro renders the page or API endpoint server-side and\n   returns the response.\n3. **If it doesn't match** — The request is passed through to the pull zone\n   origin unchanged, which serves static assets from your storage zone.\n\nThis means your static assets (CSS, JS, images, prerendered pages) are served\ndirectly from bunny.net's CDN, while dynamic pages and API routes are rendered\nat the edge.\n\n## Environment variables\n\nbunny.net Edge Scripting runs on [Deno](https://deno.com/), which exposes\nenvironment variables through `Deno.env` rather than `process.env`. The adapter\nautomatically polyfills `process.env` from `Deno.env` so that Astro and your\napplication code can access environment variables as expected.","src/content/docs/how-it-works.mdx","f486036a8293ab47","index",{"id":50,"data":52,"body":74,"filePath":75,"digest":76,"deferredRender":8},{"title":53,"description":54,"editUrl":8,"head":55,"template":10,"hero":56,"sidebar":72,"pagefind":8,"draft":12},"astro-bunny-adapter","An Astro adapter for bunny.net Edge Scripting.",[],{"tagline":57,"actions":58},"Deploy your Astro site to bunny.net's edge network with full SSR support.",[59,66],{"text":60,"link":61,"variant":62,"icon":63},"Get Started","/getting-started","primary",{"type":64,"name":65},"icon","rocket",{"text":67,"link":68,"variant":69,"icon":70},"View on GitHub","https://github.com/taobojlen/astro-bunny-adapter","minimal",{"type":64,"name":71},"github",{"hidden":12,"attrs":73},{},"import { Card, CardGrid } from \"@astrojs/starlight/components\";\n\n\u003CCardGrid>\n  \u003CCard title=\"Getting Started\" icon=\"rocket\">\n    Install the adapter and configure your Astro project.\n    [Read more →](/getting-started)\n  \u003C/Card>\n  \u003CCard title=\"Configuration\" icon=\"setting\">\n    Customize esbuild options and image handling.\n    [Read more →](/configuration)\n  \u003C/Card>\n  \u003CCard title=\"Deploying\" icon=\"external\">\n    Deploy static assets and your edge script to bunny.net.\n    [Read more →](/deploying)\n  \u003C/Card>\n  \u003CCard title=\"How It Works\" icon=\"open-book\">\n    Understand the build pipeline and request handling.\n    [Read more →](/how-it-works)\n  \u003C/Card>\n\u003C/CardGrid>","src/content/docs/index.mdx","ba089e3c286d3a72","meta::meta",["Map",79,80,81,82,83,84],"astro-config-digest","{\"root\":{},\"srcDir\":{},\"publicDir\":{},\"outDir\":{},\"cacheDir\":{},\"compressHTML\":true,\"base\":\"/\",\"trailingSlash\":\"ignore\",\"output\":\"server\",\"scopedStyleStrategy\":\"where\",\"build\":{\"format\":\"directory\",\"client\":{},\"server\":{},\"assets\":\"_astro\",\"serverEntry\":\"entry.mjs\",\"redirects\":true,\"inlineStylesheets\":\"auto\",\"concurrency\":1},\"server\":{\"open\":false,\"host\":false,\"port\":4321,\"streaming\":true,\"allowedHosts\":[]},\"redirects\":{},\"image\":{\"endpoint\":{\"route\":\"/_image\"},\"service\":{\"entrypoint\":\"astro/assets/services/noop\",\"config\":{}},\"domains\":[],\"remotePatterns\":[],\"responsiveStyles\":false},\"devToolbar\":{\"enabled\":true},\"markdown\":{\"syntaxHighlight\":false,\"shikiCo